      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       Manages all statistics data.
      4           *
      5           * @details
      6           *
      7           * The Statistics module stores information that may be useful to a diagnostic tool.
      8           *
      9           *      - Lifetime measurements
     10           *          - Lifetime data that measures the total life of the appliance components
     11           *      - Cycle measurements [ last C cycles run ]
     12           *          - Measurements that describe the behavior of completed and interrupted cycles
     13           *          - Optionally, more detailed data for the most recent last cycles
     14           *      - Fault information [ last F faults detected ]
     15           *          - Fault ID
     16           *          - Number of occurrences
     17           *          - Black box data at the time the fault occurred
     18           *          - Cycle data for the most recent cycle
     19           *          - Optionally, more detailed data for the most recent faults
     20           *      - Pre-fault information [ last P pre-faults detected ]
     21           *          - Pre-fault ID
     22           *          - Number of occurrences
     23           *          - Black box data at the time the pre-fault occurred
     24           *          - Cycle data for the most recent cycle
     25           *          - Optionally, more detailed data for the most recent pre-faults
     26           *
     27           * @copyright  Copyright 2015-2016 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     28           */
